The course is aimed to assist students in developing an understanding of the principles of academic research and writing. Within this course, we also examine the writing and formatting guidelines for master's thesis. By way of combining lectures and practical assignments, the course is supposed to lay the foundations for the development of skills needed to carry out theoretically sound and practically meaningful independent academic research.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To develop research skills and assist students in writing master's thesis in accordance with the School of Law's requirements.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  In the end of the course participant is able to: -	understand the principles of academic research; -	comprehend the fundamental notions, concepts and best practices of legal writing; -	follow the writing and formatting guidelines for master's thesis; -	orientate in main sources of academic research; -	explain the principles of research ethics.
